<item>
            <title>[LU-9738] kernel update [RHEL7.3 3.10.0-514.26.2.el7]</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-9738</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Prior to this update, a bug in the kernel prevented executables from starting&lt;br/&gt;
if the maximum process stack size (rlimit_stack) was set to a value below&lt;br/&gt;
approximately 4 MB. This update fixes the search for unmapped address ranges&lt;br/&gt;
(suitable gap) in unmapped_area() and unmapped_area_topdown() by ensuring that&lt;br/&gt;
the gap_end is always larger than gap_start. As a result, executables can be&lt;br/&gt;
started with a limited process stack size as expected. (BZ#1466138)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

</description>
